vaProduct.notes: If contract is purchase through the selling firm to which contract representative is associated, so the Annuity Date beyond age 95 cannot be extended unless contract is held through a custodial account, such as an IRA held in a custodial account. The initial and subsequent purchase payments made to the contract can be allocated to not more than 18 investment options. Additionally each allocation must be at least $500 and must be in whole numbers.

data.name: Guaranteed Withdrawal Benefit v1
data.change: Once elected may not be changed.
data.effectChangeOwnership: Change in ownership will result in termination of rider except under certain conditions.
data.gmwbCancellation: May be cancelled any 5th contract anniversary until 15th contract anniversary and on any contract anniversary thereafter.
data.gmwbTermination: Benefit will automatically terminate upon earliest of - 1) surrender, 2) annuitization, 3) change in ownership and 4) death.
data.spousalContinuationOption: Surviving spouse may elect to continue benefit after death of owner.
data.subsequentPremium: Subsequent purchase payment made during GWB purchase payment period will increase benefit base by dollar-for-dollar amount. GWB purchase payment period is 120 days from contract issue.
data.partialWithdrawals: Withdrawals will reduce benefit base in same proportion.
data.reqdMinDistributions: If RMD is larger than total guaranteed withdrawal amount multiplied by GWB Withdrawal Rate, Issuer will increase annual benefit payment to RMD amount under certain circumstances.
data.benefitDescription: Benefit guaranteed the withdrawals through annual benefit payment each year until the remaining guaranteed withdrawal amount is depleted. Benefit also offers Payment Enhancement Feature, which allows to increase the annual benefit payment for a contract year if owner is confined to a nursing home.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: Initial total guaranteed withdrawal amount is equal to initial purchase payment. Issuer increase the Total Guaranteed Withdrawal Amount by each additional Purchase Payment received during GWB Purchase Payment Period.
data.benefitBaseWithdrawal: The initial Annual Benefit Payment is equal to the initial Total Guaranteed Withdrawal Amount multiplied by the GWB Withdrawal Rate. Delay in taking first withdrawal will result in higher withdrawal rate. Annual withdrawals (including any withdrawal charge) cannot exceed the Annual Benefit Payment each Contract Year. If issuer takes an Excess withdrawal, then the Total Guaranteed Withdrawal Amount will be recalculated and it will reduce the Annual Benefit Payment to the new Total Guaranteed Withdrawal Amount in the same proportion of withdrawal reducing the account value.
data.benefitBaseEnhanceStep: The Automatic Annual Step-Up: 1) resets the Total Guaranteed Withdrawal Amount and the Remaining Guaranteed Withdrawal Amount to the Account Value on the date of the step-up, up to a maximum of $5,000,000, regardless of whether or not you have taken any withdrawals, 2) resets the Annual Benefit Payment equal to the GWB Withdrawal Rate multiplied by the Total Guaranteed Withdrawal Amount after the step-up; and 3) may reset the GWB rider charge to a rate that does not exceed the lower of: (a) the GWB Maximum Fee Rate (1.80%) or (b) the current rate that we would charge for the same rider available for new contract purchases at the time of the Automatic Annual Step-Up.
data.notes: Owner may elect to cancel the Lifetime Withdrawal Guarantee rider on the contract anniversary every five Contract Years for the first 15 Contract Years and annually thereafter. If rider is cancelled on the fifteenth contract anniversary or any contract anniversary thereafter, a Guaranteed Principal Adjustment will be added to account value. The Guaranteed Principal Adjustment is intended to restore initial investment in the contract in the case of poor investment performance. The Guaranteed Principal Adjustment is equal to (a) purchase payments credited within 120 days of the date contract is issued, reduced proportionately by the percentage reduction in account value attributable to any partial withdrawals taken minus (b) account value on the date of cancellation. The Guaranteed Principal Adjustment will be added to each applicable investment portfolio in the ratio the portion of the account value in such investment portfolio bears to the total account value in all investment portfolios and will never be less than zero. Payment Enhancement Rate is 150%. Payment Enhancement Feature is only available if the owner is age 75 or younger at contract issue.
data.chargeNotes: Charge is deducted from account value during accumulation Phase on each contract anniversary.
data.feeOption: Upon automatic step-up, Issuer may increase charge beginning after contract anniversary on which automatic step-up occurs to rate that does not exceed lower of 1) rider maximum charge, or 2) current rate for new contract purchases at step-up.
data.restrictionOnSubAcctNotes: Owner must allocate purchase payments and account value among the investment options as listed.

data.name: FlexChoice Access GLWB
data.availWhenAdded: At the time of contract issue.
data.change: Once elected may not be changed.
data.effectChangeOwnership: Change in ownership will result in termination of rider.
data.gmwbCancellation: Once elected may not be cancelled.
data.gmwbTermination: Benefit will automatically terminate upon earliest of - 1) death, 2) change in ownership, 3) account value applied to income payment, or 4) insufficient funds to deduct rider charge.
data.spousalContinuationOption: Surviving spouse may elect to continue benefit under certain conditions after death of owner.
data.subsequentPremium: Subsequent purchase payment will increase benefit base by dollar-for-dollar amount.
data.partialWithdrawals: Withdrawals will reduce benefit base in same proportion.
data.reqdMinDistributions: Issuer make available automated required minimum distribution service and systematic withdrawal program.
data.benefitDescription: Benefit guarantees lifetime income regardless of investment performance. Issuer offer two different variations of GLWB benefit 1) FlexChoice Access Level 2) Lifetime Guarantee Rate.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: Contract's account value under the rider represents the value of the investments adjusted for performance less withdrawals. The maximum amount withdrawn equals to benefit base multiplied by the guaranteed lifetime withdrawal rate (GLWB rate. Benefit base is equal to initial purchase payment thereafter increased by subsequent purchase payments and adjusted for withdrawals. Rider provides a guaranteed principal adjustment feature if the account value is decreased due to the market performance on or after the 10th contract anniversary.
data.benefitBaseNoWithdrawal: On each contract anniversary till 5th contract anniversary, if no withdrawals occurred in the previous contract year, the Benefit Base will be increased by an amount equal to the Rollup Rate (5%) multiplied by the Benefit Base before such increase.
data.benefitBaseWithdrawal: Any withdrawal taken after the lifetime withdrawal age that do not exceed the annual benefit payment will not reduce the benefit base. After the lifetime withdrawal age, the annual benefit payment is the maximum amount that may be withdrawn in the current contract year without reducing the benefit base. The initial annual benefit payment is equal to the initial benefit base multiplied by the applicable GLWB withdrawal rate.
data.benefitBaseEnhanceStep: On each contract anniversary prior to the contract Owners 91st birthday, an Automatic Annual Step-Up will occur, provided that the Account Value on that date exceeds the Benefit Base immediately before the Automatic Step-Up, The Automatic Annual Step-Up: 1) increase the Benefit Base to the Account Value on the date of the Automatic Step-Up regardless of whether or not have taken any withdrawals; 2) increase the Annual Benefit Payment to equal to the applicable GLWB Withdrawal Rate multiplied by the Benefit Base after the Automatic Step-Up; and 3) increase the GLWB rider charge to a rate that does not exceed the lower of: (a) the GLWB rider maximum charge (2.00%) or (b) the current rate that we would charge for the same rider with the same benefits, if available for new contract purchases at the time of the Automatic Step-Up.
data.notes: Owner may elect to cancel the Lifetime Withdrawal Guarantee rider on the contract anniversary every five Contract Years for the first 10 Contract Years and annually thereafter. If rider is cancelled on the fifteenth contract anniversary or any contract anniversary thereafter, a Guaranteed Principal Adjustment will be added to account value. The Guaranteed Principal Adjustment is intended to restore initial investment in the contract in the case of poor investment performance. The Guaranteed Principal Adjustment is equal to (a) purchase payments credited within 120 days of the date contract is issued, reduced proportionately by the percentage reduction in account value attributable to any partial withdrawals taken minus (b) account value on the date of cancellation. The Guaranteed Principal Adjustment will be added to each applicable investment portfolio in the ratio the portion of the account value in such investment portfolio bears to the total account value in all investment portfolios and will never be less than zero.
data.chargeNotes: Issuer impose charge of 1.35% of benefit base, deducted for the prior contract year on contract anniversary prior to taking into account any automatic step-up by withdrawing amounts on a pro rata basis from enhanced dollar cost averaging program balance and account value in the separate account.
data.feeOption: Upon automatic step-up, Issuer may increase charge beginning after contract anniversary on which automatic step-up occurs to rate that does not exceed a maximum 2.00% of the benefit base.

data.name: Flex Choice
data.availWhenAdded: No longer available for new purchases.
data.change: Once elected may not be changed.
data.effectChangeOwnership: Change in ownership will result in termination of rider.
data.gmwbCancellation: May be cancelled on contract anniversary every 5 contract years until 10 contract years and annually thereafter.
data.gmwbTermination: Benefit will automatically terminate upon earliest of - 1) death, 2) change in ownership, 3) account value applied to income payment, or 4) insufficient funds to deduct rider charge.
data.spousalContinuationOption: Surviving spouse may elect to continue benefit under certain conditions after death of owner.
data.subsequentPremium: Subsequent purchase payment will increase benefit base by dollar-for-dollar amount.
data.partialWithdrawals: Withdrawals will reduce benefit base in same proportion.
data.reqdMinDistributions: Issuer make available automated required minimum distribution service and systematic withdrawal program.
data.benefitDescription: Benefit guarantees lifetime income regardless of investment performance. Issuer offer two different variations of GLWB benefit 1) FlexChoice Level, and 2) FlexChoice Expedite.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: The initial Benefit Base is equal to initial Purchase Payment and increases the Benefit Base by each additional Purchase Payment. Contract's account value under the rider represents the value of the investments adjusted for performance less withdrawals. Benefit base is equal to initial purchase payment thereafter increased by subsequent purchase payments and adjusted for withdrawals. Rider offers two variations 1) Level and 2) Expedite, any one them can be opted at the time of electing the rider.
data.benefitBaseNoWithdrawal: On each contract anniversary till 10th contract anniversary, if no withdrawals occurred in the previous contract year, the Benefit Base will be increased by an amount equal to the Rollup Rate (5%) multiplied by the Benefit Base before such increase.
data.benefitBaseWithdrawal: Excess withdrawals would reduce the benefit base and future total guaranteed withdrawal amount. The maximum amount withdrawn equals to benefit base multiplied by the guaranteed lifetime withdrawal rate (GLWB rate).
data.notes: For joint life, spouse's date of birth may not be more than 10 years after owner's date of birth. If account value is reduced to zero on or after lifetime withdrawal age because of non-excess withdrawal, Issuer will pay any remaining annual benefit payment in effect at the time account value is reduced to zero. Effective as of next contract anniversary, Issuer will then begin making monthly payments, using the applicable GLWB lifetime guarantee rate multiplied by benefit base, for rest of owners life. If account value is reduced to zero, no death benefit will be available. GLWB lifetime guarantee rate for FlexChoice level for single life is same as GLWB withdrawal rate and for joint life it is 1.00% less.
data.otherInfo: The rider provides a death benefit in addition to the base contract death benefit.
data.chargeNotes: Issuer impose charge of 1.20% of benefit base, deducted for the prior contract year on contract anniversary prior to taking into account any automatic step-up by withdrawing amounts on a pro rata basis from enhanced dollar cost averaging program balance and account value in the separate account.
data.feeOption: Upon automatic step-up, Issuer may increase charge beginning after contract anniversary on which automatic step-up occurs to rate that does not exceed lower of 1) rider maximum charge, or 2) current rate for new contract purchases at step-up.

data.notes: During accumulation phase, owner can make unlimited transfers with no charge, but reserve right to limit this in future - Contract allows to no charge for the first 12 transfers in a year thereafter the fee is $25 per transfer and currently waiving the transfer fee. During Income phase, transfers are restricted from Fixed Account to Sub-Account. Transfers in more then 18 Sub- accounts are restricted if the request is made by telephone or internet, more then 18 transfers can be made by calling or writing.

vaWithdrawals.notes: During the Accumulation Phase, the owner can a make withdrawal from the contract. If the amount withdrawn is determined to include the withdrawal of any of prior Purchase Payments, a withdrawal charge is assessed against each Purchase Payment withdrawn. The free withdrawal amount for each Contract Year after the first (there is no free withdrawal amount in the first Contract Year) is equal to 10% of total Purchase Payments, less the total free withdrawal amount previously withdrawn in the same Contract Year.

data.notes: Owner may elect the Systematic Withdrawal Program at any time and withdraw maximum up to 10% of total purchase payment. During first contract year, owner can receive payments monthly and quarterly only.

vaSchdTransAssetRebalancings.notes: Available only during the Accumulation phase and allows to automatically rebalance Account Value to return to original percentage allocations.

vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.notes: Available only during the Accumulation phase and allows to systematically transfer a set amount each month from Investment Portfolios to other available Investment Portfolios.
vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.dcaCancellation: May be cancelled any time after election.
vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.dcaTermination: May be terminated any time after election.

vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.notes: Owner may allocate only new purchase payments to Enhanced Dollar Cost Averaging account. Owner may choose from 6 months and 12 months transfers. Owner may also elect Three Month Market Entry Program, for 3 months duration.
vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.dcaCancellation: May be cancelled any time after election.
vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.dcaTermination: May be terminated any time after election.

data.notes: If an annuity option is not elected, Issuer will apply Life Annuity with 10 years of guaranteed Annuity Payments.
